events.description: The Rashidun Caliphate is effectively ended with the assassination of Ali, the last caliph.
events.html: • 661 – The Rashidun Caliphate is effectively ended with the assassination of Ali, the last caliph.[1]

events.description: The 6.4–7.1 .mw-parser-output .tooltip-dotted{border-bottom:1px dotted;cursor:help}Mw Lisbon earthquake kills about thirty thousand people.
events.html: • 1531 – The 6.4–7.1 Mw Lisbon earthquake kills about thirty thousand people.[2][3]

events.description: The Council of Trent establishes an official distinction between Roman Catholicism and Protestantism.
events.html: • 1564 – The Council of Trent establishes an official distinction between Roman Catholicism and Protestantism.[4]

events.description: The Grand Duchy of Lithuania defeats the Tsardom of Russia in the Battle of Ula during the Livonian War.
events.html: • 1564 – The Grand Duchy of Lithuania defeats the Tsardom of Russia in the Battle of Ula during the Livonian War.[5]

events.description: For the first time, the Ottoman Empire permanently cedes territory to the Christian powers.
events.html: • 1699 – For the first time, the Ottoman Empire permanently cedes territory to the Christian powers.[6]

events.description: The 8.7–9.2 Mw Cascadia earthquake takes place off the west coast of North America, as evidenced by Japanese records.
events.html: • 1700 – The 8.7–9.2 Mw Cascadia earthquake takes place off the west coast of North America, as evidenced by Japanese records.[7]

events.description: The British First Fleet, led by Arthur Phillip, sails into Port Jackson (Sydney Harbour) to establish Sydney, the first permanent European settlement on Australia. Commemorated as Australia Day.
events.html: • 1788 – The British First Fleet, led by Arthur Phillip, sails into Port Jackson (Sydney Harbour) to establish Sydney, the first permanent European settlement on Australia. Commemorated as Australia Day.[8]

events.description: The Rum Rebellion is the only successful (albeit short-lived) armed takeover of the government in New South Wales.
events.html: • 1808 – The Rum Rebellion is the only successful (albeit short-lived) armed takeover of the government in New South Wales.[9]

events.description: Michigan is admitted as the 26th U.S. state.
events.html: • 1837 – Michigan is admitted as the 26th U.S. state.[10]

events.description: Gordon Bremer takes formal possession of Hong Kong Island at what is now Possession Point, establishing British Hong Kong.
events.html: • 1841 – Gordon Bremer takes formal possession of Hong Kong Island at what is now Possession Point, establishing British Hong Kong.[11]

events.description: Point No Point Treaty is signed in Washington Territory.
events.html: • 1855 – Point No Point Treaty is signed in Washington Territory.[12]

events.description: First Battle of Seattle: Marines from the USS Decatur drive off American Indian attackers after all-day battle with settlers.
events.html: • 1856 – First Battle of Seattle: Marines from the USS Decatur drive off American Indian attackers after all-day battle with settlers.[13]

events.description: American Civil War: The state of Louisiana secedes from the Union.
events.html: • 1861 – American Civil War: The state of Louisiana secedes from the Union.[14]

events.description: American Civil War: General Ambrose Burnside is relieved of command of the Army of the Potomac after the disastrous Fredericksburg campaign. He is replaced by Joseph Hooker.
events.html: • 1863 – American Civil War: General Ambrose Burnside is relieved of command of the Army of the Potomac after the disastrous Fredericksburg campaign. He is replaced by Joseph Hooker.[15]

events.description: American Civil War: Governor of Massachusetts John Albion Andrew receives permission from the Secretary of War to raise a militia organization for men of African descent.
events.html: • 1863 – American Civil War: Governor of Massachusetts John Albion Andrew receives permission from the Secretary of War to raise a militia organization for men of African descent.[16]

events.description: Reconstruction Era: Virginia is readmitted to the Union.
events.html: • 1870 – Reconstruction Era: Virginia is readmitted to the Union.[17]

events.description: Troops loyal to The Mahdi conquer Khartoum, killing the Governor-General Charles George Gordon.
events.html: • 1885 – Troops loyal to The Mahdi conquer Khartoum, killing the Governor-General Charles George Gordon.[18]

events.description: The world's largest diamond ever, the Cullinan, which weighs 3,106.75 carats (0.621350 kg), is found at the Premier Mine near Pretoria in South Africa.
events.html: • 1905 – The world's largest diamond ever, the Cullinan, which weighs 3,106.75 carats (0.621350 kg), is found at the Premier Mine near Pretoria in South Africa.[19]

events.description: The Rocky Mountain National Park is established by an act of the U.S. Congress.
events.html: • 1915 – The Rocky Mountain National Park is established by an act of the U.S. Congress.[20]

events.description: Finnish Civil War: A group of Red Guards hangs a red lantern atop the tower of Helsinki Workers' Hall to symbolically mark the start of the war.
events.html: • 1918 – Finnish Civil War: A group of Red Guards hangs a red lantern atop the tower of Helsinki Workers' Hall to symbolically mark the start of the war.[21]

events.description: The first demonstration of the television by John Logie Baird.
events.html: • 1926 – The first demonstration of the television by John Logie Baird.[22]

events.description: The Indian National Congress declares 26 January as Independence Day or as the day for Poorna Swaraj ("Complete Independence") which occurred 17 years later.
events.html: • 1930 – The Indian National Congress declares 26 January as Independence Day or as the day for Poorna Swaraj ("Complete Independence") which occurred 17 years later.[23]

events.description: The Apollo Theater reopens in Harlem, New York City.
events.html: • 1934 – The Apollo Theater reopens in Harlem, New York City.[24]

events.description: German–Polish declaration of non-aggression is signed.
events.html: • 1934 – German–Polish declaration of non-aggression is signed.[25]

events.description: Spanish Civil War: Catalonia Offensive: Troops loyal to nationalist General Francisco Franco and aided by Italy take Barcelona.
events.html: • 1939 – Spanish Civil War: Catalonia Offensive: Troops loyal to nationalist General Francisco Franco and aided by Italy take Barcelona.[26]

events.description: World War II: The first United States forces arrive in Europe, landing in Northern Ireland.
events.html: • 1942 – World War II: The first United States forces arrive in Europe, landing in Northern Ireland.[27][28]

events.description: World War II: Audie Murphy displays valor and bravery in action for which he will later be awarded the Medal of Honor.
events.html: • 1945 – World War II: Audie Murphy displays valor and bravery in action for which he will later be awarded the Medal of Honor.[29]

events.description: The Hale Telescope at Palomar Observatory sees first light under the direction of Edwin Hubble, becoming the largest aperture optical telescope (until BTA-6 is built in 1976).
events.html: • 1949 – The Hale Telescope at Palomar Observatory sees first light under the direction of Edwin Hubble, becoming the largest aperture optical telescope (until BTA-6 is built in 1976).[30][31]

events.description: The Constitution of India comes into force, forming a republic. Rajendra Prasad is sworn in as the first President of India. Observed as Republic Day in India.
events.html: • 1950 – The Constitution of India comes into force, forming a republic. Rajendra Prasad is sworn in as the first President of India. Observed as Republic Day in India.[32]

events.description: Black Saturday in Egypt: rioters burn Cairo's central business district, targeting British and upper-class Egyptian businesses.
events.html: • 1952 – Black Saturday in Egypt: rioters burn Cairo's central business district, targeting British and upper-class Egyptian businesses.[33]

events.description: Soviet Union cedes Porkkala back to Finland.
events.html: • 1956 – Soviet Union cedes Porkkala back to Finland.[34]

events.description: The 41-acre (17 ha) Chain Island is listed for sale by the California State Lands Commission, with a minimum bid of $5,226.
events.html: • 1959 – The 41-acre (17 ha) Chain Island is listed for sale by the California State Lands Commission, with a minimum bid of $5,226.[35]

events.description: Ranger 3 is launched to study the Moon. The space probe later misses the Moon by 22,000 miles (35,400 km).
events.html: • 1962 – Ranger 3 is launched to study the Moon. The space probe later misses the Moon by 22,000 miles (35,400 km).[36]

events.description: The three Beaumont children disappear from a beach in Glenelg, South Australia, resulting in one of the country's largest-ever police investigations.
events.html: • 1966 – The three Beaumont children disappear from a beach in Glenelg, South Australia, resulting in one of the country's largest-ever police investigations.[37]

events.description: JAT Flight 367 is destroyed by a terrorist bomb, killing 27 of the 28 people on board the DC-9. Flight attendant Vesna Vulović survives with critical injuries.
events.html: • 1972 – JAT Flight 367 is destroyed by a terrorist bomb, killing 27 of the 28 people on board the DC-9. Flight attendant Vesna Vulović survives with critical injuries.[38]

events.description: Turkish Airlines Flight 301 crashes during takeoff from Izmir Cumaovası Airport (now İzmir Adnan Menderes Airport), killing 66 of the 73 people on board the Fokker F28 Fellowship.
events.html: • 1974 – Turkish Airlines Flight 301 crashes during takeoff from Izmir Cumaovası Airport (now İzmir Adnan Menderes Airport), killing 66 of the 73 people on board the Fokker F28 Fellowship.[39]

events.description: The Ugandan government of Tito Okello is overthrown by the National Resistance Army, led by Yoweri Museveni.
events.html: • 1986 – The Ugandan government of Tito Okello is overthrown by the National Resistance Army, led by Yoweri Museveni.[40]

events.description: Mohamed Siad Barre is removed from power in Somalia, ending centralized government, and is succeeded by Ali Mahdi.
events.html: • 1991 – Mohamed Siad Barre is removed from power in Somalia, ending centralized government, and is succeeded by Ali Mahdi.[41]

events.description: Lewinsky scandal: On American television, U.S. President Bill Clinton denies having had "sexual relations" with former White House intern Monica Lewinsky.
events.html: • 1998 – Lewinsky scandal: On American television, U.S. President Bill Clinton denies having had "sexual relations" with former White House intern Monica Lewinsky.[42]

events.description: The 7.7 Mw Gujarat earthquake shakes Western India, leaving 13,805–20,023 dead and about 166,800 injured.
events.html: • 2001 – The 7.7 Mw Gujarat earthquake shakes Western India, leaving 13,805–20,023 dead and about 166,800 injured.[43][44]

events.description: Diane Whipple, a lacrosse coach, is killed in a dog attack in San Francisco. The resulting court case clarified the meaning of implied malice murder.
events.html: • 2001 – Diane Whipple, a lacrosse coach, is killed in a dog attack in San Francisco. The resulting court case clarified the meaning of implied malice murder.[45]

events.description: Rioting breaks out in Antananarivo, Madagascar, sparking a political crisis that will result in the replacement of President Marc Ravalomanana with Andry Rajoelina.
events.html: • 2009 – Rioting breaks out in Antananarivo, Madagascar, sparking a political crisis that will result in the replacement of President Marc Ravalomanana with Andry Rajoelina.[46][47]

events.description: Nadya Suleman gives birth to the world's first surviving octuplets.
events.html: • 2009 – Nadya Suleman gives birth to the world's first surviving octuplets.[48]

events.description: An aircraft crashes at Los Llanos Air Base in Albacete, Spain, killing 11 people and injuring 21 others.
events.html: • 2015 – An aircraft crashes at Los Llanos Air Base in Albacete, Spain, killing 11 people and injuring 21 others.[49]

events.description: Syrian civil war: The People's Protection Units (YPG) recaptures the city of Kobanî from the Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant (ISIL), marking a turning point in the Siege of Kobanî.
events.html: • 2015 – Syrian civil war: The People's Protection Units (YPG) recaptures the city of Kobanî from the Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant (ISIL), marking a turning point in the Siege of Kobanî.[50][51]

entities.name: Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant

events.description: A Sikorsky S-76B flying from John Wayne Airport to Camarillo Airport crashes in Calabasas, 30 miles west of Los Angeles, killing all nine people on board, including five-time NBA champion Kobe Bryant and his daughter Gianna Bryant.
events.html: • 2020 – A Sikorsky S-76B flying from John Wayne Airport to Camarillo Airport crashes in Calabasas, 30 miles west of Los Angeles, killing all nine people on board, including five-time NBA champion Kobe Bryant and his daughter Gianna Bryant.[52]

events.description: Protesters and farmers storm the Red Fort near Delhi, clashing with police. One protester is killed and more than 80 police officers are injured.
events.html: • 2021 – Protesters and farmers storm the Red Fort near Delhi, clashing with police. One protester is killed and more than 80 police officers are injured.[53]
